(GULPS)

21:54.447 --> 21:55.715
Where is he?

21:56.883 --> 21:58.217
Flavor Station.

22:06.826 --> 22:08.194
(URINATING RESUMES)

22:21.608 --> 22:23.776
MAN: (ON TV) Shut up...
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

22:25.011 --> 22:26.913
(WOMAN ON TV
TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

22:47.266 --> 22:49.101
Cut up my food?
Why?

22:58.578 --> 23:00.179
(UTENSILS SCRAPING)

23:00.212 --> 23:01.614
It's fine, Eugene.

23:04.617 --> 23:06.085
(SCRAPING CONTINUES)

23:06.853 --> 23:08.054
Stop it!

23:08.087 --> 23:09.355
If you really
wanna help,

23:09.388 --> 23:10.723
maybe you should
do like they said,

23:10.757 --> 23:12.625
and go ahead,
and finish the
goddamn job.

23:56.636 --> 23:58.004
(CLICKS)

23:59.105 --> 24:00.306
(POWERS DOWN)

24:13.319 --> 24:15.354
QUINCANNON:
I've been up all night,

24:15.387 --> 24:18.024
thinking about the mistakes
I've made in my life.

24:18.057 --> 24:20.159
All right,
I've been selfish,

24:20.192 --> 24:21.861
I've been short-sighted.

24:23.162 --> 24:26.866
Long time ago
I slipped into despair
and I lost my way.

24:28.000 --> 24:31.403
Since then,
I haven't been
my best self.

24:31.437 --> 24:33.272
But now, that's no excuse

24:33.305 --> 24:36.008
because, now,
it's high time
to make amends.

24:37.109 --> 24:38.745
I'm happy to hear it.

24:38.778 --> 24:41.080
And you, Mr. Mayor,

24:41.113 --> 24:43.215
you really raked me
over the coals.

24:43.249 --> 24:45.484
Yes, you did.
Yes, you did.

24:45.518 --> 24:47.720
But, but
you were right.

24:47.754 --> 24:51.157
This town is in trouble,
it needs help.

24:51.190 --> 24:54.326
Now, I'm sorry
I wasn't able
to hear that at the time.

24:54.360 --> 24:56.062
I got defensive, I...
(SIGHS)

24:56.095 --> 24:57.363
...pulled my pants down.

24:58.798 --> 25:01.433
And I reacted.
No, it's, it's fine.

25:01.467 --> 25:04.070
I needed a new
briefcase anyway.
It was childish.

25:04.103 --> 25:05.972
I meant to reach out
after church Sunday,

25:06.005 --> 25:07.807
but with the
crowds and all I...

25:07.840 --> 25:09.341
Busiest I've seen
it in a long time.

25:10.242 --> 25:12.078
You went to church, sir?

25:12.444 --> 25:13.546
Yep.

25:13.580 --> 25:14.747
Jesse Custer's church?

25:15.447 --> 25:17.049
Yes, I did.

25:17.083 --> 25:19.919
Now, your
Green Acre people?

25:19.952 --> 25:21.187
You think they'll
meet with me?

25:21.220 --> 25:22.855
MILES: Absolutely.

25:22.889 --> 25:25.958
QUINCANNON: I've asked
around, and you're right,
they're highly regarded.

25:25.992 --> 25:29.662
There comes a time
when we all need
to move into the future.

25:29.696 --> 25:32.732
And, uh, now it's my time.

25:32.765 --> 25:36.435
MILES: And their president,
uh, Jerry, is definitely
one of the good guys.

25:36.468 --> 25:38.404
I think you'll get along.

25:38.437 --> 25:39.471
QUINCANNON: Sure.

25:39.505 --> 25:41.107
MILES: His whole team is...

25:41.140 --> 25:42.842
(INDISTINCT TALKING)

25:44.276 --> 25:45.277
What did he say?

25:47.046 --> 25:48.047
Who?
The Preacher.

25:48.547 --> 25:49.649
What'd he say?

25:51.918 --> 25:53.152
What'd he say?

25:56.188 --> 25:57.757
(YELLS) What'd he say to you?

25:59.358 --> 26:01.193
He said to
serve God, Donnie.

26:01.227 --> 26:03.830
Which I will,
from this day on.

26:03.863 --> 26:04.864
That okay?

26:07.700 --> 26:08.868
Any more
questions you'd

26:08.901 --> 26:11.070
care to shout at me
in front of the Mayor?
(CHUCKLES)

26:12.104 --> 26:13.539
(FAINT MUSIC
PLAYING FROM RADIO)

26:13.873 --> 26:15.708
Sorry.

26:15.742 --> 26:17.977
So, I can come to them,
they can come to me,

26:18.010 --> 26:19.245
whichever's easiest.

26:19.278 --> 26:21.213
I'll give them a call today.
Thank you.

26:22.682 --> 26:25.251
To a new beginning, Mr. Mayor.

26:25.284 --> 26:26.318
For me...
(KNOCKS ON TABLE)

26:26.352 --> 26:27.586
...and this town.

26:30.923 --> 26:34.426
Ooh, how the sun shines
when you take time
to look at it.

26:36.095 --> 26:37.096
Yeah.

26:37.630 --> 26:38.631
(SLURPS)

26:40.232 --> 26:42.534
(SMACKS AND EXHALES)

26:42.568 --> 26:45.071
JESSE: So you feel that
she's intruding?

26:45.104 --> 26:47.774
Exactly.
She's intruding.

26:47.807 --> 26:49.676
I mean, just because
I made, what I
now realize,

26:49.709 --> 26:51.978
the terrible mistake
of marrying her daughter

26:52.011 --> 26:54.881
doesn't give her
the right to tell me
how to bring up my kid.

26:54.914 --> 26:57.316
When to put him to bed,
how to dress him...

26:57.349 --> 26:58.450
I think the key here is...

26:59.318 --> 27:00.319
Be patient.

27:03.055 --> 27:04.056
You're right.

27:05.257 --> 27:07.626
Just be patient.

27:07.660 --> 27:09.395
Thanks, Preacher.
Anytime.

27:09.428 --> 27:10.596
Who's next?
How can I help you?

27:10.629 --> 27:11.630
Excuse me.

27:12.398 --> 27:13.900
Excuse me.

27:13.933 --> 27:15.501
I got a real problem...
(CLEARS THROAT)
...I could use some help.

27:19.205 --> 27:20.372
Well, let's hear it.

27:21.540 --> 27:24.376
My problem is
I like bad boys.

27:25.044 --> 27:26.045
One in particular.

27:27.413 --> 27:28.781
For instance,

27:28.815 --> 27:32.584
me and this bad boy,
we used to run these
weird-ass reptiles

27:32.618 --> 27:34.486
for a Mexican cartel
down in Miami.

27:34.520 --> 27:36.322
Rare collector items.

27:36.355 --> 27:39.591
And one day
we deliver a Komodo dragon

27:39.625 --> 27:42.729
to the buyer, this
Rasta guy, who keeps
looking me up and down.

27:42.762 --> 27:43.830
And, I mean,
who can blame him?

27:43.863 --> 27:46.866
(CHUCKLES) But
bad boy doesn't like it,

27:46.899 --> 27:49.668
so puts his 9mm
right to the head
of the Komodo dragon,

27:49.702 --> 27:50.837
and he warns Rasta,

27:51.771 --> 27:54.273
"You keep checking
out my girl's ass,

27:54.306 --> 27:56.776
"I'ma shoot
the lizard in the face."

27:56.809 --> 27:59.645
But Rasta's got some balls
and he says,

27:59.678 --> 28:02.114
"Hey, man,
she don't
want me looking,

28:02.148 --> 28:04.884
"she shouldn't put
that booty on
in the morning."

28:04.917 --> 28:08.220
So my bad boy, he pets
the Komodo dragon one time,

28:08.821 --> 28:09.889
and then...

28:09.922 --> 28:11.457
Blam!
(GASPS)

28:11.490 --> 28:12.691
Blows its brains out.

28:12.725 --> 28:13.960
They were gonna
eat that dragon anyways.

28:13.993 --> 28:15.094
You don't know that...

28:15.127 --> 28:16.628
They were setting up
a barbecue spit.

28:16.662 --> 28:17.663
That's not the point.

28:18.765 --> 28:20.432
The point is, this guy

28:20.466 --> 28:23.135
shot a Komodo dragon
in the head.

28:23.803 --> 28:27.606
This guy is bad. B-A-D.

28:27.639 --> 28:29.408
And now he's
acting like he's not.

28:29.441 --> 28:33.045
He's denying who he is,
and that's my problem.

28:35.081 --> 28:36.182
No. It's okay.

28:38.317 --> 28:40.820
I've done worse than that.
Uh, yeah, much worse.

28:40.853 --> 28:42.989
If you guys
had any idea...

28:43.022 --> 28:44.456
And look
at me now, Tulip.

28:46.692 --> 28:47.693
Really look,

28:48.928 --> 28:49.929
and be honest.

28:52.131 --> 28:53.332
I have changed.

28:54.200 --> 28:55.434
You see that, right?

28:57.136 --> 28:59.105
Which means
you can change too.

28:59.138 --> 29:00.239
I know you can.

29:00.272 --> 29:02.775
We don't have to
be what we've been.

29:05.845 --> 29:06.846
You can be good.

29:08.815 --> 29:10.649
That's what we want, right?
We...

29:12.584 --> 29:13.886
We all wanna be good.

29:13.920 --> 29:15.521
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

29:15.554 --> 29:16.755
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

29:18.024 --> 29:20.226
Something outside
wants to talk to you.

29:21.193 --> 29:22.261
Excuse me?

29:22.294 --> 29:23.930
I told it,
it can't come in.

29:26.398 --> 29:28.567
Wait. You're coming
back though, right?

29:29.568 --> 29:31.237
I'm not going anywhere.

29:37.776 --> 29:39.178
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

29:42.949 --> 29:45.317
Keep it away
from the windows,
people are eating.

29:48.754 --> 29:49.755
(SIGHS)

29:50.622 --> 29:51.958
Hey, Eugene.

29:53.792 --> 29:54.827
What's up?

30:08.774 --> 30:09.775
What's going on?

30:15.747 --> 30:16.748
That's not true.

30:21.553 --> 30:22.554
I don't hate you.

30:23.355 --> 30:24.356
(CHUCKLES)

30:51.884 --> 30:53.385
We'll think of something.

30:57.723 --> 30:58.724
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

31:02.361 --> 31:03.362
Hey.

31:04.696 --> 31:06.465
I was hoping to
talk to you about something.

31:06.498 --> 31:08.134
Of course.

31:08.167 --> 31:11.237
But could you
pray with Tracy first?

31:11.270 --> 31:12.972
We do every day,
but you were the only one

31:13.005 --> 31:15.307
who made such
wonderful progress.

31:15.341 --> 31:18.610
You know, I guess
my thing can wait a
couple of minutes, so...

31:18.644 --> 31:19.878
sure.

31:20.479 --> 31:21.747
I'll see what I can do.

31:21.780 --> 31:22.781
Thank you.

31:28.720 --> 31:30.089
Son of a bitch.

31:33.192 --> 31:35.127
(SCREAMING) I told you,
you come back here,
I'll kill you!

31:35.894 --> 31:37.296
MRS. LOACH:
You murderer!

31:37.329 --> 31:38.664
Get out of the car!

31:39.398 --> 31:40.699
Get out of the car!

31:41.767 --> 31:43.435
Calm down,
I brought him here.

31:44.670 --> 31:45.671
Never come back!

31:46.372 --> 31:47.539
MRS. LOACH:
Murderer!

31:47.573 --> 31:48.640
(GRUNTING)

31:48.674 --> 31:49.675
Drop it.

31:52.478 --> 31:53.879
(PANTING)

31:56.782 --> 31:57.783
I'll kill you!

31:59.485 --> 32:01.720
I'll kill you,
you murderer!

32:01.753 --> 32:02.854
Murderer!

32:02.888 --> 32:04.256
Step away
from the car.

32:09.228 --> 32:10.629
JESSE: Come on, Eugene.
MRS. LOACH: Murderer!

32:11.630 --> 32:13.932
Come on.
(HOARSELY) Murderer!

32:13.966 --> 32:15.968
It's okay. I promise.

32:19.705 --> 32:21.140
Murderer!

32:21.173 --> 32:23.609
MRS. LOACH: How dare you
show your face here?

32:23.642 --> 32:25.477
Now, this has
gone on too long.

32:25.511 --> 32:27.046
I told you
never come back.

32:27.079 --> 32:28.947
This boy has made
a terrible mistake.

32:28.981 --> 32:30.016
You're sick.

32:30.049 --> 32:31.617
And he's suffering.
You murderer!

32:32.651 --> 32:33.819
You're suffering too...

32:38.690 --> 32:39.725
Forgive him.

33:11.890 --> 33:15.327
BETSY: A 66?
Last time I checked,
that's a "pass."

33:15.361 --> 33:17.363
(CHEWING)
That's a good pass.

33:17.396 --> 33:18.997
That teacher's always
picking on Chris.

33:19.031 --> 33:20.566
I don't know why
or what her problem is.

33:21.567 --> 33:23.702
Other than her
husband's disgustingly fat.

33:28.107 --> 33:29.708
It's good to be
back, right?

33:32.478 --> 33:34.946
Yeah. We're working
on some new deal.

33:34.980 --> 33:37.349
I don't really
know nothing.

33:39.218 --> 33:41.920
Did you know Mr. Quincannon
was at church on Sunday?

33:41.953 --> 33:42.954
Yeah, I heard.

33:49.228 --> 33:51.263
You're moping, Donnie.

33:52.231 --> 33:53.232
What is it?

33:56.268 --> 33:57.603
Baby, what's going on?

33:57.636 --> 33:58.637
(ENGINE STARTS
IN THE DISTANCE)

34:00.072 --> 34:01.073
Speak.

34:01.873 --> 34:03.409
Preacher's got a power.

34:03.942 --> 34:04.976
What?

34:05.010 --> 34:06.778
A power.

34:06.812 --> 34:09.281
(BREATH TREMBLING)
He made me do things. And...

34:11.183 --> 34:13.285
(STAMMERING)
Linus, the bus driver...

34:13.319 --> 34:14.320
And, um...

34:15.687 --> 34:17.856
I think Mr. Quincannon, too.
I don't...

34:18.724 --> 34:20.592
I don't know how he does it.

34:20.626 --> 34:23.095
But there's nothing
I could do, Bets...

34:23.129 --> 34:24.296
There's nothing I...

34:27.533 --> 34:29.601
He made me put
a gun in my mouth,

34:30.369 --> 34:32.371
and I couldn't stop him.

34:33.905 --> 34:36.742
I was just a puppet,
I was just...

34:36.775 --> 34:39.445
(STUTTERING) A cow in a maze.

34:39.478 --> 34:41.880
Wait. Preacher put a gun
in your mouth?

34:41.913 --> 34:44.883
No, no. I put
the gun in my mouth.

34:45.617 --> 34:47.919
And he made me do it.

34:47.953 --> 34:50.256
I cocked the trigger,
and I was gonna pull it.

34:50.289 --> 34:54.826
But his power, it made me,

34:55.494 --> 34:56.895
in my mind.

34:56.928 --> 34:58.697
(WHIMPERS AND SOBS))

34:58.730 --> 34:59.931
(BETSY SHUSHING)

34:59.965 --> 35:01.367
It's okay.

35:01.400 --> 35:03.001
(MAN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

35:03.435 --> 35:04.436
It's okay.

35:06.805 --> 35:09.508
Please don't screw
Russell in accounting.

35:10.642 --> 35:12.311
I won't, baby.

35:15.214 --> 35:17.883
Don't you worry
about Preacher.

35:17.916 --> 35:20.986
Sooner or later,
your moment will come

35:21.019 --> 35:23.322
and he'll get
what he deserves.

35:23.355 --> 35:25.457
(WHISTLING
WYNKEN, BLYNKEN, AND NOD)

35:34.466 --> 35:37.169
Well, your dad's
been suffering, right?

35:38.637 --> 35:39.638
Worrying over you?

35:42.408 --> 35:44.310
Well, now you can tell him
not to worry anymore.

35:47.646 --> 35:48.680
You're welcome.

35:50.649 --> 35:52.351
(WHISTLING CONTINUES)

35:53.219 --> 35:54.320
(EXHALES)

36:01.227 --> 36:03.229
(TRAIN HORN BLOWING
IN THE DISTANCE)

36:53.679 --> 36:55.180
(PHONE RINGING)
"On top of the situation.

36:55.213 --> 36:57.883
"Don't worry,
we'll be back soon."

36:57.916 --> 36:59.918
Remember, they love you.
(RINGING CONTINUES)

37:01.152 --> 37:02.954
Ready?
Yeah.

37:02.988 --> 37:03.989
Let's do this.

37:04.823 --> 37:06.191
(RINGING STOPS)

37:21.473 --> 37:22.641
(WOMAN TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

37:22.674 --> 37:25.076
Thank you, Les.
Nice one.
Thank you for that.

37:25.110 --> 37:26.478
You found the
hardware store.

37:27.546 --> 37:28.680
WOMAN: Goodnight.

37:28.714 --> 37:30.882
WOMAN 2: See you later,
Cassidy.
I, uh...

37:30.916 --> 37:32.017
I took the scenic route.

37:32.851 --> 37:34.119
Got you a present.

37:38.256 --> 37:40.091
Oh, Lassie, that's so sweet.

37:41.493 --> 37:42.628
Are we going steady now?

37:43.462 --> 37:44.963
Even better.

37:46.332 --> 37:47.833
We're in love.

37:49.100 --> 37:51.169
(HEAVY BREATHING)

37:53.472 --> 37:54.706
(CREAKING)

38:04.149 --> 38:06.017
This is a recurring
issue for us.

38:06.051 --> 38:09.187
I say no screen time
unless the homework
is done first.

38:09.220 --> 38:11.423
And my point is
if he gets the
homework done quickly,

38:11.457 --> 38:13.024
he gets extra screen time.

38:13.058 --> 38:14.760
I like the carrot,
not the stick.

38:16.127 --> 38:17.128
What would you advise?

38:18.063 --> 38:19.865
Just use your
best judgment.

38:21.500 --> 38:22.768
SHERIFF HUGO: Preacher.

38:22.801 --> 38:24.836
These gentlemen
from the government need
to speak with you.

38:26.905 --> 38:28.474
Cathy, Bill.

38:28.507 --> 38:29.508
Thank you.

38:34.079 --> 38:35.947
Thank you.
You can go now.

38:37.983 --> 38:38.984
(JESSE SIGHS)

38:47.659 --> 38:48.760
This about Dallas?

38:48.794 --> 38:50.496
You know what it's about.

38:51.597 --> 38:52.931
Who are you?

38:52.964 --> 38:55.133
We gave you the
money for the drugs
and the whore-mongering.

38:55.166 --> 38:56.702
And the
black beauties...

38:56.735 --> 38:58.637
We've been patient,
we gave you
everything you

38:58.670 --> 39:00.639
wanted, but now
we're out of time.

39:00.672 --> 39:02.107
We need what's
inside of you.

39:02.140 --> 39:04.610
We've told you
this repeatedly.

39:07.446 --> 39:09.381
Guys, I've never
met you before in my life.

39:10.181 --> 39:12.651
Not you. We told
your best friend.

39:13.419 --> 39:16.154
Skinny, pale, sickly?

39:17.523 --> 39:19.090
We told him
it's not to be used.

39:19.124 --> 39:20.926
And you've been
using it. A lot.

39:23.194 --> 39:24.996
Where exactly
are you guys from?

39:25.030 --> 39:26.031
Exactly?

39:27.032 --> 39:28.066
We're from heaven.

39:28.567 --> 39:29.968
Both of us.

39:30.001 --> 39:31.002
Heaven?

39:33.672 --> 39:35.340
As in the sky above?

39:35.941 --> 39:36.942
Is there another?

39:37.876 --> 39:39.911
We watched you. We waited.

39:40.345 --> 39:41.813
Now, we're here.

39:41.847 --> 39:45.951
You are in possession
of an enormous power.

39:45.984 --> 39:47.152
DEBLANC: We need it back.

39:51.490 --> 39:54.059
What is this?
It lives in there.

39:57.395 --> 39:59.164
Guys...(EXHALES DEEPLY)

39:59.197 --> 40:01.166
I've seen a lot of
weird stuff in my life.

40:01.199 --> 40:04.035
I mean, more than
my fair share. But...

40:04.069 --> 40:06.137
I've never, not one time,

40:06.171 --> 40:08.940
heard of God fitting himself
into a can of Old Timer.

40:11.176 --> 40:12.511
I think he thinks...

40:14.780 --> 40:16.615
No, no, no,
you don't understand.

40:17.315 --> 40:18.750
What's inside of you...

40:19.651 --> 40:20.919
It isn't God.

40:24.556 --> 40:27.158
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)
(COUNTRY MUSIC
PLAYING FROM SPEAKERS)

40:27.192 --> 40:29.595
Well, here they are.
Welcome. Come in, come in.

40:29.628 --> 40:31.463
Odin Quincannon,
this is Justin Driver.

40:31.497 --> 40:33.465
Justin.
VP of sustainability.

40:33.499 --> 40:35.233
Chloe Newbold, VP branding.
Hi.

40:35.266 --> 40:37.302
And this is
Jerry Cutler, President
of Green Acre Group.

40:37.335 --> 40:38.737
Jerry Cutler,
nice to meet you.

40:38.770 --> 40:41.006
There's one more coming.
He's in the bathroom.

40:41.039 --> 40:43.308
Okay. And you
all know Miles Person,

40:43.341 --> 40:45.110
VP of taking care
of business.

40:45.143 --> 40:47.345
(ALL CHUCKLING)
Come on in, take a seat.

40:47.378 --> 40:48.647
It's after 6:00 p.m.,

40:48.680 --> 40:51.817
so, uh, unfortunately
the brandies
are mandatory.

40:51.850 --> 40:52.851
(CHUCKLING)

40:53.785 --> 40:55.754
Listen, I'm really glad
y'all are here.

40:56.555 --> 40:58.456
I've been thinking, and,

40:58.490 --> 40:59.725
well, heck,
this is just something

40:59.758 --> 41:01.960
we should've made happen
